#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:4
msgid "Spin: NumPy’s developer tool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:6
msgid ""
"NumPy uses a command-line tool called ``spin`` to support common development "
"tasks such as building from source, running tests, building documentation, "
"and managing other developer workflows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:11
msgid ""
"The ``spin`` tool provides a consistent interface for contributors working "
"on NumPy itself, wrapping multiple underlying tools and configurations into "
"a single command that follows NumPy’s development conventions. Running the "
"full test suite::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:16
msgid "$ spin test -m full"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:18
msgid "Running a subset of tests::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:20
msgid "$ spin test -t numpy/_core/tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:22
msgid "Running tests with coverage::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:24
msgid "$ spin test --coverage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:26
msgid "Building the documentation::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/spin.rst:28
msgid "$ spin docs"
msgstr ""
